Class TreeInsertChildren

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventListener, javax.faces.component.PartialStateHolder, javax.faces.component.StateHolder, javax.faces.event.ComponentSystemEventListener, javax.faces.event.FacesListener, javax.faces.event.SystemEventListenerHolder

    public class TreeInsertChildren
extends TreeFamily
    TreeInsertChildren is an UIComponent that represents the insertion point for the children of a parent tree node which is represented by TreeNodeItem.

    This component does not allow any children.

    Author:
    Bauke Scholtz
    See Also:
    TreeNodeItem
